            </msItem>
            <msItem xml:id="a24" n="26">
              <locus from="148a"/>
              
              <title xml:lang="en">The history of Eupraxia (or Euphrasia)</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܬܫܥܝܬܐ ܕܥܠ ܩܕܝܫܬܐ ܘܢܨܝ̣ܚܬ̇ ܒܕܘܒܪ̈ܝܗ̇ ܐܘܦܪܘܟܣܝܐ.</rubric>
              <note>See the <bibl>Acta Sanctt. for March, t. ii., p. 265.</bibl>
              </note>
            </msItem>
            <msItem xml:id="a25" n="27">
              <locus from="162a"/>
              
              <title xml:lang="en">The history of Hilaria, the daughter of the emperor
                Zeno</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܬܫܥܝܬܐ ܕܥܠ ܩܕܝܫܬܐ ܐܠܐܪܝܐ ܒܪܬܗ ܕܙܝܢܘܢ ܡ̇ܠܟܐ</rubric>
              <note>In this manuscript the names were originally Maria ($ܡܐܪܝܐ) and Theodosius
                (ܬܐܘܕܘܣܝܣ), but they have been altered throughout by a later hand</note>
              <note>See <bibl>Add. 14,641, no. 4, h.</bibl>
